getCurrentTransactionsToProcess

public java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> getCurrentTransactionsToProcess(java.lang.String ECSpecName)
                                                                      throws java.lang.Exception
Lists the transaction IDs that are pending processing by a given Event Cycle. Algorithm:
  1. get EPCIS query filtering rule from local vocabulary by calling configure.get with params class="vocabulary", type="urn:orange:filteringRule", id=<ECSpecName>
    function returns filtering parameters, e.g.
    • prior bizStep urn:epcglobal:cbv:bizStep:shipping
    • prior shipping:deliverySgln <bizLocation/ID of receiving place>
    • next bizStep urn:epcglobal:cbv:bizStep:receiving
    • next bizLocation/ID <bizLocation/ID of receiving place>
    • bpeMask <business transaction type mask>
  2. query all Business Process events matching bpeMask
  3. query EPCIS events with filtering parameters + no EPCIS event related to next step
  4. extract transaction IDs from matching EPCIS events

Specified by:
getCurrentTransactionsToProcess in interface Access
Parameters:
ECSpecName - name of event cycle to run (e.g. "reception2eme")
Returns:
ArrayList of transaction IDs (e.g. ("urn:epcglobal:cbv:bt:shipo:0000187784","urn:epcglobal:cbv:bt:shipo:0000187027")
Throws:
java.lang.Exception - "Misconfiguration" exception if no local vocabulary is available
java.lang.Exception - "No business events to process" exception if no local bpevent is available
java.lang.Exception - "No pending EPC events" exception if no remote EPC events are
